                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 St. Pierre-Miquelon/424: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-13T15:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 13, 1936—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 13—2:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1105. Department’s telegram No. 453, November 10 noon. Foreign Office states that
                    it has never heard of the question of operating a distillery in St. Pierre but
                    that when the discussion of the proposed <pb facs="0514" n="434" xml:id="pg_434"
                    /> decree and the resolution takes place between the various ministries it will
                    see to it that some provision is taken to prevent such a thing.</p>
                <p>Without regard to the exportation of French alcohol known as “trois-six” the
                    Foreign Office states that if the resolution as now drafted is approved the
                    importation of trois-six into St. Pierre will be prohibited since it is a
                    “foreign alcohol.”</p>
                <p>The Foreign Office has promised to inform the Embassy when the decree and the
                    resolution come up for discussion.</p>
                <p>Please inform Treasury.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
